    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix KDF test function signature mismatch and missing utilities\n\n### Summary\nThe KDF test was failing to compile and execute correctly due to several issues:\n1. Missing `test_util.h` header with hex conversion utilities\n2. Incorrect function call signature to `kdf()` function\n3. Memory leaks from allocated hex buffers\n4. Improper key padding for KDF function\n\nThis fix addresses all these issues to make the KDF tests work correctly.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/TEST/test_kdf.c`: Fixed function call to match `kdf()` signature, added proper key padding, and memory cleanup\n- `openair3/TEST/test_util.h`: Created new header with hex conversion utilities and HL macro implementation\n\nWhen running the KDF tests, users were experiencing crashes due to undefined HL macro and incorrect parameter passing to the kdf function. The test would compile but fail at runtime with segmentation faults when trying to process the test vectors.\n\nAfter this fix, the KDF tests should compile and run correctly, properly validating the key derivation function implementation against RFC 4231 test vectors.\n"
}